      <!-- ===== GENERAL INFORMATION ===== -->
      <section class="prog-intro">

        <div class="prog-intro-card">
          <h2>Nursery</h2>
          <p>The Herbarius nursery is open from <strong>16 March to 27 June 2026</strong> (every day from 9:30 am to noon).</p>
          <p>Edible plants, aromatics, edible flowers, wild salads, perennial vegetables, medicinal plants — our collections will amaze you!</p>
          <p><em>(With any plant purchase, a free self-guided tour of the gardens is included)</em></p>
        </div>

        <div class="prog-intro-card">
          <h2>Visits</h2>
          <p>Outside the listed activities, the garden welcomes visitors all year round for self-guided tours (5 EUR), by appointment only, preferably by email at <a href="mailto:f.goulley@herbarius.net">f.goulley@herbarius.net</a> or by text message to <a href="tel:+33603432528">06.03.43.25.28</a></p>
        </div>

        <div class="prog-intro-card">
          <h2>Gift vouchers</h2>
          <p>Looking for a special gift or a moment to recharge?</p>
          <p>With our gift vouchers, offer a peaceful retreat to rest, discover, and savour...</p>
          <p>We have many options: a night in a treehouse facing the sea, a discovery or in-depth workshop on alternative gardening, a guided tour of the medieval garden, or edible, aromatic or medicinal plants.</p>
          <p>Prices and conditions on request at <a href="mailto:f.goulley@herbarius.net">f.goulley@herbarius.net</a></p>
        </div>

      </section>

